    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="875"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/421.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Written statement has been made by Lange that he will not resign until after
                    receivership has been actually established, and he has held post of Receiver and
                    Vice Consul together for some time. This caused Liberian Government to instruct
                    Dinklage, Liberian Chargé d’Affaires at Berlin, by mail July 17, to urge again
                    German Foreign Office to withdraw Lange’s appointment as Vice Consul. Should
                    this fail he is to intimate to German Foreign Office that Liberian Government
                    will be compelled to revoke Lange’s exequatur whenever receivership becomes
                    actually operative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crum.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
